.jumbotron
  .container
    .row
      .col-md-8
        %h2 KO Pool
        %p The system is in TEST MODE.  {{display_authorized()}}.
        %p There are currently {{active_pool_entries_count}} teams remaining in the ring, battling for a sum of ${{total_pot}}!
        %p
          %a.btn.btn-primary.btn-lg{href: "#/users/register", role: "button"} Register »
      .col-md-4
        %img.img-rounded.frontpage-logo{alt: "KO Pool Logo", src: asset_path('kopool_c_med.png')}
.container
  / Example row of columns
  .row
    .col-md-12
    .lead.text-center {{web_state.broadcast_message}}
  .row

    .col-md-4
      .btn-group{:dropdown => ""}
        %button.btn.btn-danger{:type => "button"} View Matchups
        %button.btn.btn-danger.dropdown-toggle{:type => "button"}
          %span.caret
          %span.sr-only Split button
        %ul.dropdown-menu{:role => "menu"}
          %li{"ng-repeat"=>"week in weeks"}
            %a{href:"#/weeks/{{week.id}}/matchups"}
              Week {{week.week_number}}
      %p Use this go go directly to the matchups for any week.
      %p

    .col-md-4
      %h2 Your Picks This Week
      %p This doesn't actually work yet, but this is what I'm envisioning for User Choices.
      %p
        %a.btn.btn-primary{"ng-click" => "go('/nfl_teams')", role: "button"} Your Picks »
    .col-md-4
      %h2 Your Teams
      %p This doesn't actually work yet, but this is what I'm envisioning for User Choices.
      %p
        %a.btn.btn-primary{"ng-click" => "go('/nfl_teams')", role: "button"} Your Teams »

  .row
    .col-md-4
      %h2 Profile
      %p This doesn't actually work yet, but this is what I'm envisioning for User Choices.
      %p
        %a.btn.btn-primary{"ng-click" => "go('/nfl_teams')", role: "button"} Your Profile »

  .row
    .col-sm-12.text-center
      %h4 Admin Panel
    .col-md-4
      %h2 NFL Teams
      %p Administrators can use this 'NFL Teams' button to view, edit, and update NFL teams.  Make sure the teams are all in the correct Conference and Division.  Upload a nice looking logo for each team.  Any logo you upload will automatically be stored on your Amazon S3 account and will automatically be scaled to "Medium" (300x300) and "Thumbnail" (100x100) sizes.
      %p
        %a.btn.btn-primary{"ng-click" => "go('/nfl_teams')", role: "button"} NFL Teams »
    .col-md-4
      %h2 Weeks (Season 1)
      %p Administrators can use this 'Weeks' button to view, edit, and update weeks.  Make sure all of the dates are correct.  You must always enter and edit them in international format: yyyy-mm-dd.  Also, currently there is a bug where the timezone is messing up the weeks.  You may have to enter hours also:  yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm.  Jack and Dave will discuss.
      %p
        %a.btn.btn-success{href: "#/seasons/1/weeks", role: "button"} Season 1 Weeks »
    .col-md-4
      %h2 Matchups (Week 1)
      %p This is the admin page for creating matchups. You can create and edit matchups for a certain week, as well as save the outcomes of the games.
      %p
        %a.btn.btn-info{href: "#/weeks/1/matchups/admin", role: "button"} Week 1 Matchups »
  .row
    .col-md-4
      %h2 Commissioner
      %p Commissioner maintenance page - for the commish only!  Lets you open/close a week for picks and also move to the next week.
      %p
        %a.btn.btn-info{href: "#/admin/web_state", role: "button"} Commissioner »

  %hr/
